description.plain:
“Not Like I’m In Love With You” is a song by American singer Lauren Weintraub, released on April 29, 2022, by Half-Pint Dynamite Records from her debut extended play This Is Your Brian On Love. Capping the project with a spitfire singalong, “Not Like I’m in Love with You” (nearly 6M streams to date) offers up a catchy, pop-infused take on the confusion around falling for a best friend, highlighting Weintraub’s spunky personality alongside a catchy hook that is sure to become a live fan-favorite.

As the flagship songwriter signed to Brandy Clark’s publishing company, All BC Music, Weintraub is busy making waves in Music City and beyond — already amassing 34M+ streams and being named a HITS Magazine “One To Watch” for 2022. Armed with vulnerable lyrics, a sassy demeanor and raw, unmatched vocals, the 24-year-old continues to captivate fans around the globe, garnering more than 700k+ followers across social media and earning a nomination for “TikTok Songwriter of the Year” at this year’s iHeartRadio Awards.

annotations:
I know I love right, keep it tight
 I’m a good kisser
She knows that there is nothing wrong with herself.

Thought I wasn’t good enough
 But that wasn’t what it was (Ah, ah)
 It’s almost a relief
 There’s nothing wrong with me (Ah, ah)
She thought that the reason her boyfriend wasn’t attracted to her was because something was wrong with her, but then she made the connection and determined that it’s not her, it’s her gender.
But you didn’t notice
Her boyfriend didn’t show any more attraction toward her dress than he does when she doesn’t dress up because he likes boys.

Showed up in a tight dress
 Thinking you’d be helpless all night
She thought that her boyfriend would go crazy (in other terms, get aroused) seeing her in a dress that was so tight it probably accentuated her curves nicely.
But how come my spoon’s always bigger?

This is likely referring to the cuddling position.

From Google: The best way to describe spooning is to lie on your side and wrap your partner in a big hug, with your arm resting over their waist. Or, if you’re the little spoon, your partner will be hugging you.



If you look at that picture, the “big spoon” is the person in the blue, and the “little spoon” is the other person.

Typically, in heterosexual relationships (a male and a female), the male is the “big spoon” and the female is the “little spoon”. This is because most (not all) females crave the feeling of safety, and the male is the one that gives them that protection. It is not often that the female is the “big spoon” for the male.

In homosexual relationships (a male and an male, or a female and another female), there is one who likes that calmness, and one who likes providing it.

Therefore, the lyric saying that the female is the “big spoon” most of the time, is saying that the male is the one who craves affection, which is predominately seen in homosexual relationships.
Pictured him undressed at the same time
this is lauren talking about how her and her boyfriend were both attracted to the same guy and it helped her realise her boyfriend was gay

description.plain:
Makeup Is Expensive is a single released by Lauren Weintraub on August 6, 2021. It was first teased on her tiktok as she said “Okay Hold up,,, I know you agree with me on this one”.

The song illustrates the feeling Weintraub has over the current dating vs hookup culture. “makeup is expensive” is eluding to how expensive it is to waste makeup such as mascara while crying over guys.
